<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-292-213  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 292 213.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Jan 30 1989 v23 n4 pS32(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bechtel consolidates its global reach with satellite links toremote sites. (Special Report: Communications Innovators)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gill, Philip J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Bechtel Group Inc no longer relies on megaprojects for thebulk of its revenue.andP;  Instead, the company relies on numeroussmaller projects, and to handle the communications needs of suchprojects Bechtel is investing in satellites.andP;  The company is alsoconsidering using very small aperture terminals (VSATs) in orderto set up communications systems quickly in remote regions.andO;Bechtel states that it uses MCI's fiber links whenever possiblebut that satellite links are necessary where fiber links are notavailable.andP;  Bechtel will maintain its hybrid network since itallows the company the option of shifting back and forth betweenterrestrial and satellite links as price and performancetrade-offs change.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bechtel Group Inc. (communication systems).andO;Topic:     Satellite CommunicationsConstruction industryNetworksVery Small Aperture Terminals.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>